Package: disk-toolkit
Version: 1.0.0
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: bash (>= 4.0), coreutils, util-linux, zenity, pv, openssl, gzip, e2fsprogs, ntfs-3g, parted, policykit-1
Recommends: pigz, xfsprogs, btrfs-progs, partclone, gparted, openssh-client, libglib2.0-bin
Maintainer: Disk Toolkit Maintainers <RonaldMedvecz@gmail.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/RonaldMedvecz/Disk-ToolKit
Description: Wipe, clone, and image disks with a GUI or terminal interface
 Disk Toolkit is a single self-contained script providing four disk
 operations through either a zenity-based GUI or a terminal fallback:
 .
  * Secure wipe (parallel random overwrite, zero-fill, or hardware
    secure-erase where supported)
  * Disk cloning that adapts to source/destination size differences,
    including automatic filesystem growth into extra destination space
  * ISO/backup image creation with destination free-space checking and
    optional gzip compression
  * Restoring a captured image back onto a drive
 .
 Includes NTFS consistency checking and best-effort automatic repair
 before any resize, with a guided fallback to Windows chkdsk and GParted
 when automatic repair isn't possible.
